About the Product:
Handlooms of India are as colourful and vibrant as their culture. Steeped in folklore, romancing the age-old ethos of the people while keeping up with the contemporary, the handlooms of India have a long history that can be traced to ancient times. Traversing the onslaught of time and changing of powers and dynasties, the handlooms of India have not only thrived but reinvented themselves to give each region of the country an identity and pride. Tata Tea Premium comes with a unique blend of tea crafted by experts that tea lovers across India will enjoy. This special edition pack of Tata Tea Premium is part of a collection celebrating Independence Day. Each pack design has been inspired by a famous handloom style of India.
This pack features the Panja Durries weaving style by Khem Raj Sundriyal of Panipat. Woven on two parallel bars of the loom, durries are rugs used for household purposes. Panja Durries get their name from a claw like weaving tool called Panja. Thick fabrics are a speciality of Haryana, as climatic conditions do not allow the use of fine threads. Make your tea breaks indulgent with a sip of Tata Tea Premium.

Title: Narasus Coffee - Dhivyam Premium, Coarse Ground Filter Coffee, 500 g Pouch
About the Product:
South Indian Coffee, also known as Filter Coffee is a sweet milky coffee made from dark roasted coffee beans (70%-80%) and chicory (20%-30%), especially popular in the southern states of Andhra Pradesh, Karnataka, Kerala and Tamil Nadu.
